  "definition": {
    "en": "Guanethidine Sulfate, when dried, contains not less than 98."
  },
  "appearance": {
    "en": "Guanethidine Sulfate occurs as white, crystals or crystalline powder. It is odorless or has a slight, character-istic odor and a bitter taste. It is very soluble in formic acid, freely soluble in water, and practically insoluble in ethanol (95) and in diethyl ether. Melting point: 251 – 2569C (an evacuated sealed capillary tube, with decomposition)."
  },
  "testSpecification": [
    {
      "@type": "IdentificationSpecification",
      "testName": {
        "en": "Identification"
      },
      "testType": "TestType-Identification",
      "testConditions": {
        "en": "(1) To 4 mL of a solution of Guanethidine Sulfate (1 in 4000) add 2 mL of 1-naphthol TS, 1 mL of dia-cetyl TS and 15 mL of water, and allow to stand for 30 minutes: a red color develops. Determine the infrared absorption spectrum of Guanethidine Sulfate, previously dried, as directed in the po-tassium bromide disk method under Infrared Spectropho-tometry <2.25>, and compare the spectrum with the Refer-ence Spectrum: both spectra exhibit similar intensities of absorption at the same wave numbers. A solution of Guanethidine Sulfate (1 in 10) responds to Qualitative Tests <1.09> for sulfate. pH <2.54> Dissolve 1.0 g of Guanethidine Sulfate in 50 mL of water: the pH of the solution is between 4.7 and 5.7."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "PuritySpecification",
      "testName": {
        "en": "Purity"
      },
      "testType": "TestType-Purity",
      "testConditions": {
        "en": "(1) Clarity and color of solution—Dissolve 1.0 g of Guanethidine Sulfate in 50 mL of water: the solution is clear and colorless. (2) Methylisothiourea sulfate—Dissolve 2.0 g of Guanethidine Sulfate in 80 mL of sodium hydroxide TS, and allow to stand for 10 minutes. Add 60 mL of hydrochloric acid, 2 g of sodium bromide and water to make 200 mL. Then, to this solution add 0.70 mL of 1/60 mol/L potassium bromate VS and 2 mL of zinc iodide-starch TS: a blue color develops. Each mL of 0.1 mol/L perchloric acid VS ＝ 29.64 mg of C10H22N4.H2SO4"
      }
    }
  ],
  "storageConditions": {
    "en": "Containers—Tight containers. Storage—Light-resistant."
  }
}